{"TopicId":160244,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"How to make almost perfect square out of any rectangle","CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-05T21:18:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-05T21:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first thing you need to do is Isosceles right triangle which is fairly easy, after that fold points with 45\u00B0 to the one with 90\u00B0. \u00A0It will be perfect as long as you do it perfectly (So almost no time) But it should only differ 2mm at max.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSide of square will be\u00A0the lenght of shorter side of t\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Er\u003C/span\u003Eiangle /2\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E(a leg?)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EHope some of you don\u0027t know this already\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EPicture of where you should fold thr triangle (A and B to C)\u003Cbr\u003E\nanyone who has idea how to properly calculate differences in surface area (from my creations it is something around 5,6 times smaller)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022214f81eab19847f142b4ca87d2567288.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022651\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/214f81eab19847f142b4ca87d2567288.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nStep by step\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/gallery/Dk3ic\u0022 style=\u0022height:899px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0